    "body": "<!-- .github/pull_request_template.md -->\r\n\r\n## 📌 Description\r\n\r\nAdd all reduce benchmark to benchmark trtllm and trtllm_mnnvl_ar perf \r\n\r\n**Example**\r\n```\r\nmpirun -np 4 python benchmarks/flashinfer_benchmark.py         --routine allreduce_fusion         --num_tokens 64 --hidden_size 4096      \r\n[INFO] AllReduce benchmark: world_size=4, gpus_per_node=4\r\n/usr/local/lib/python3.12/dist-packages/torch/distributed/c10d_logger.py:83: UserWarning: barrier(): using the device under current context. You can specify `device_id` in `init_process_group` to mute this warning.\r\n  return func(*args, **kwargs)\r\n[INFO] Created workspace: backend=mnnvl, shape=(64, 4096)\r\n[PERF] mnnvl_allreduce_oneshot:: median time 0.011 ms; std 0.057 ms; achieved tflops nan TFLOPs/sec; achieved tb_per_sec 0.068 TB/sec\r\n[PERF] mnnvl_allreduce_twoshot:: median time 0.011 ms; std 0.431 ms; achieved tflops nan TFLOPs/sec; achieved tb_per_sec 0.070 TB/sec\r\n```\r\n\r\n## 🔍 Related Issues\r\n\r\n<!-- Link any related issues here -->\r\n\r\n## 🚀 Pull Request Checklist\r\n\r\nThank you for contributing to FlashInfer! Before we review your pull request, please make sure the following items are complete.\r\n\r\n### ✅ Pre-commit Checks\r\n\r\n- [x] I have installed `pre-commit` by running `pip install pre-commit` (or used your preferred method).\r\n- [ ] I have installed the hooks with `pre-commit install`.\r\n- [x] I have run the hooks manually with `pre-commit run --all-files` and fixed any reported issues.\r\n\r\n> If you are unsure about how to set up `pre-commit`, see [the pre-commit documentation](https://pre-commit.com/).\r\n\r\n## 🧪 Tests\r\n\r\n- [x] Tests have been added or updated as needed.\r\n- [x] All tests are passing (`unittest`, etc.).\r\n\r\n## Reviewer Notes\r\n\r\n<!-- Optional: anything you'd like reviewers to focus on, concerns, etc. -->\r\n\r\n\r\n<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\n## Summary by CodeRabbit\n\n* **New Features**\n  * Added an AllReduce fusion benchmark: multi-backend, multi-pattern, multi-GPU distributed runs with configurable tokens/hidden-size/dtypes and optional correctness validation; integrated as a selectable routine.\n* **Chores**\n  * Extended benchmark output with AllReduce-specific columns and improved backend name formatting for clearer performance tables and bandwidth metrics.\n* **Documentation**\n  * Added README section with flags and launch examples for the new AllReduce benchmark.\n<!-- end of auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->",
